overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The
  assistant began by conducting a thorough code review to understand the
  existing styling, identifying areas such as the color palette, typography,
  layout, and form elements that needed refinement. A new sleep-themed color
  palette was introduced, along with custom utility classes for gradients and
  shadows. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and the
  progress bar were redesigned for a more polished look. The main questionnaire
  form and the intro section were overhauled with decorative elements and
  improved visual hierarchy. During the process, a console error related to null
  input values was identified and fixed by modifying the  component to
  safely handle  values. Finally, the user highlighted remaining color
  inconsistencies, leading to a comprehensive update of all alert styles,
  section grouping borders, and hardcoded colors within the report section to
  ensure a cohesive and calming aesthetic throughout the entire application.
